{
  "texts": [
    "These approaches include penetration, peeling fruit flesh/mesocarp, chemical applying reaction or exertion of external force on a fruit.",
    "Figure 3 illustrates some of the commonly adopted instruments for destructive testing of fruit maturity.",
    "Based on the actual measurement performed, this study classifies destructive methods as either physical or chemical.",
    "Physical approaches do not include chemical reactions during the process.",
    "Hence, they can be named as non-chemical approaches as well."
  ]
}